Recently saw a talk between two turbonormies in a comments section and one of them asked like: "Who is our generation's Kate Bush?", but the other rebuked: "Kate Bush is our generation's Kate Bush, she is still alive". Struck me as quite profound. The living presence of the old.

Like Trump saying life starts at 80. We should have faith in the old to still be able to surprise us on occasion, to be relevant, to have something new to say. Alex Colville's art is about it. The dignity of living as if you were young, in spite of the crude incidentality of time
